Place Name: Mine Creek Civil War Battlefield State Historic Site
Description: The museum did have some interesting artifacts, information and beautiful trails.  We were also warned about ticks.  Make sure that you spray yourself before you go on the trails.

Place Name: Battle Of Island Mound State Historic Site
Description: Easy stop, quick visit, but a cool piece of history. The trail was well maintained and the bathroom was also well maintained.  Check out my instagram post on this site: @mikeisoutside
Mostly cut down trails.  Half shaded.  One of the bridges worries me but otherwise it's a pleasant area.  Lots of ticks this year.

Place Name: Mine Creek Battlefield Interpretive Walking Trail

Description: This is a great resource for breast cancer patients especially but for anyone really. They have a little bit of everything. Clothing, wigs, scarves, bras, pillow protectors for your seatbelt after surgery, handbags, hats, other assorted post mastectomy supplies, jewelry; really something for everyone. The owner & everyone working the store are so kind & helpful. Great place to shop & to donate to

Beautiful and healthy prairie with a diverse range of wildflowers, grasses, and wildlife. The whole area has a great history (you can see clear evidence of the Santa Fe Trail) and there is a QR code you can scan on your phone for an audio tour along the trail if you so choose!
A very well put together and maintained museum depicting the civil war. The walking trails through the battlefield are well kept and easy to maneuver
